<subSubSection id="F004F371FBF1520A743DF524AED511F3" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DCA53C39AC06205945ABE8A4FF9F8FC5" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81334513ED83AF598814404EE3303C35" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Based on external characters, no close relatives were recovered in the phylogenetic analysis of morphological characters by 
<bibRefCitation id="310076B3AAB3C5800321942B8FA9F710" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Reemer and 
<normalizedToken id="EC2E8ACCD457B13DD257C562904E9049" originalValue="StÃ¥hls">Stahls</normalizedToken>
(in press)
</bibRefCitation>
. The species is characterized by its metallic blue colouration and golden pilosity, a long basoflagellomere, a medially widely bare face, a rectangular postero-apical corner of wing cell r4+5, and unfused tergites 3 and 4. The latter character may indicate affinity with 
<taxonomicName id="B9EEC8309A7F43E0770CDEBAA15596E4" authority="Wiedemann, 1824" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ceratophya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ceratophya" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ceratophya</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AE3E523AB12D45D98EAF53EC3D537F20" authority="Hull, 1944" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Kryptopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Kryptopyga" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kryptopyga</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="0C2059269626D0DCB1C9357A63AD34BD" authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Thompsodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thompsodon" order="Diptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thompsodon</taxonomicName>
, but the species lacks other diagnostic characters for these taxa. This species is left unplaced for now.
</paragraph>
